Izawa, the war is bringing in a new situation.

494
01:11:33,871 --> 01:11:36,428
And that is an "information attack. "

495
01:11:36,463 --> 01:11:41,051
It'll change from operations information to fighting information which we'll use as a weapon.

496
01:11:41,552 --> 01:11:44,054
But the weak point in this plan is...

497
01:11:44,555 --> 01:11:47,349
It's only a system with no substance.

498
01:11:48,058 --> 01:11:51,318
It's lacking attractive contents.

499
01:11:51,353 --> 01:11:54,856
We call it pioneering a new media, but...

500
01:11:54,891 --> 01:11:58,360
it still can't compete with the old films.

501
01:11:58,395 --> 01:11:59,361
Don't you think so?

502
01:12:02,364 --> 01:12:05,833
That's why we have to re-envision film.

503
01:12:05,868 --> 01:12:14,084
But the upper class are losing their sensitivity and passion for cinema.

504
01:12:14,251 --> 01:12:18,411
So I want to entrust this with the younger generation.

505
01:12:19,811 --> 01:12:20,811
What do you think?

506
01:12:21,811 --> 01:12:23,811
Don't you have any interest in my proposal?

507
01:12:26,851 --> 01:12:30,491
But I'm just a directing assistant.

508
01:12:32,211 --> 01:12:37,491
Well, certainly it may be unusual for me to have this kind of conversation
with someone I don't know well.

509
01:12:38,411 --> 01:12:46,011
But, seeing you, I was reminded of my own youth.

510
01:12:47,811 --> 01:12:50,251
"I was like him too once... "

511
01:12:52,611 --> 01:12:58,251
I was defiant back then and was always arguing.

512
01:12:58,286 --> 01:13:01,251
I was bullied often.

513
01:13:03,251 --> 01:13:06,691
There. The cigarette burns are still left.

514
01:13:09,411 --> 01:13:13,176
I got in an argument with one of my seniors and he burnt me with his cigarette.

515
01:13:13,211 --> 01:13:21,531
Well, I was bullied and bullied. And, as I was thinking up excuses, I became a skilled producer.

516
01:13:23,211 --> 01:13:28,331
So, when I met you, it just came to me.

517
01:13:29,131 --> 01:13:30,651
How do I say this?

518
01:13:31,651 --> 01:13:33,651
You were so transparent...

519
01:13:34,811 --> 01:13:35,811
Izawa.

520
01:13:36,651 --> 01:13:37,811
I can feel it.

521
01:13:38,251 --> 01:13:42,251
The beautiful energy that flows out of you.

522
01:13:42,731 --> 01:13:44,051
A flow of clear energy...

523
01:13:45,731 --> 01:13:47,611
I'm interested in you.

524
01:13:49,611 --> 01:13:52,611
I'd like to take a risk with you.

525
01:13:52,646 --> 01:13:53,611
What do you think?

526
01:13:54,611 --> 01:13:55,851
Won't you join me?

527
01:14:02,251 --> 01:14:04,536
What do you want me to do?

528
01:14:04,571 --> 01:14:07,176
First there's planning. I need a screenplay.

529
01:14:07,211 --> 01:14:13,211
It's alright if it's just temporary, but can you work something out by next Thursday?

530
01:14:15,131 --> 01:14:18,151
Please freely write about something daring.

531
01:14:18,186 --> 01:14:21,171
Those kinds of things are always the best.

532
01:14:23,171 --> 01:14:30,371
Don't worry. If I must say, I'm the most flexible producer around here.

533
01:14:30,651 --> 01:14:34,171
Well, I am a little eccentric.

534
01:14:35,171 --> 01:14:36,171
Izawa.

535
01:14:37,171 --> 01:14:38,771
I'm looking forward to your work.

536
01:14:39,531 --> 01:14:42,691
Youth have to produce the good stuff.

537
01:16:49,691 --> 01:16:50,651
Is something wrong?

538
01:16:50,691 --> 01:16:56,131
Uh, no. I wonder what it could be. Maybe there are rats in this house or something...

539
01:17:29,171 --> 01:17:34,571
The last couple in the world is walking towards the world's end.

540
01:17:34,606 --> 01:17:41,291
The two continued on and on through the cold wind.

541
01:17:42,651 --> 01:17:45,211
They finally arrived at the world's end.

542
01:17:45,246 --> 01:17:47,771
It was the mountain where God lives.

543
01:17:48,771 --> 01:17:54,851
They climbed the mountain, put pepper on their lips, and prayed for the world to end.

544
01:17:56,971 --> 01:17:59,171
Everything disappeared.

545
01:18:00,171 --> 01:18:07,531
Mountains... Men... Women... Colors... Even light...

546
01:18:09,171 --> 01:18:14,771
Then God appeared and blessed the couple.

547
01:18:16,571 --> 01:18:22,171
Then God remade the world again.

548
01:18:23,971 --> 01:18:27,171
Eternally new...

549
01:18:28,171 --> 01:18:31,171
very nostalgic...

550
01:20:18,171 --> 01:20:23,771
Attention. Today's studio inspection has been cancelled.

551
01:20:29,171 --> 01:20:31,211
An accident occurred.

552
01:20:32,771 --> 01:20:37,571
Ochiai's head was directly struck by some lighting, almost as if he had been targeted.

553
01:20:49,171 --> 01:20:55,171
Everyone in the establishment was brought together
and my colleague, Yoshida, was suddenly chosen as the new director.

554
01:20:55,206 --> 01:20:58,691
No one had even imagined he'd have been singled out for director.

555
01:20:58,726 --> 01:21:01,971
It all proceeded as if it were part of some movie scenario.

556
01:21:02,691 --> 01:21:04,971
Once again my days of boredom had returned.

557
01:23:00,171 --> 01:23:01,171
Sorry...

558
01:23:25,771 --> 01:23:27,171
Push harder.

559
01:23:28,651 --> 01:23:29,171
Push.

560
01:24:56,171 --> 01:25:02,691
It was during a day off at midday when, from far off, a bombing attack began.

561
01:25:02,726 --> 01:25:08,171
Since we didn't have a bomb shelter, we hid in my closet.

562
01:28:19,211 --> 01:28:25,891
I had written a screenplay about a 27-year old directing assistant who was living with an idiot woman.

563
01:28:26,891 --> 01:28:30,891
Had I written the truth? Or did what I write become the truth?

564
01:28:30,926 --> 01:28:33,371
I myself didn't even know.

565
01:28:42,171 --> 01:28:44,411
This is a pretty difficult project...

566
01:28:44,691 --> 01:28:46,771
I don't mean that it's bad, but...

567
01:28:48,171 --> 01:28:50,491
I wonder if the television viewers will understand it...

568
01:28:53,491 --> 01:28:55,491
Don't misunderstand me.

569
01:28:56,491 --> 01:28:58,456
I don't hate this kind of stuff.

570
01:28:58,491 --> 01:29:01,491
I mean, there are a lot of worthless programs on TV.

571
01:29:01,526 --> 01:29:04,491
I think that literary movies are essential.

572
01:29:05,691 --> 01:29:07,491
This is a novel idea.

573
01:29:08,491 --> 01:29:10,491
How do I say this?

574
01:29:13,211 --> 01:29:16,491
I just wonder whether the average viewer will understand this.

575
01:29:17,491 --> 01:29:20,531
Because viewers are incredibly stupid.

576
01:29:21,531 --> 01:29:24,891
But more than that, I wonder what the intellectual community would say about this...

577
01:29:25,691 --> 01:29:28,891
It might be quite difficult to make money with this.

578
01:29:31,691 --> 01:29:35,891
For the mean time, let's use this as a basis and leave the screenplay to a professional.

579
01:29:36,971 --> 01:29:38,211
It might change quite a bit...

580
01:29:40,891 --> 01:29:45,211
To be honest, I don't really know whether this is interesting or not...

581
01:29:48,691 --> 01:29:49,656
Izawa

582
01:29:49,691 --> 01:29:51,656
I'm not saying this is impossible.

583
01:29:51,691 --> 01:29:55,211
This kind of project is decided by its main star.

584
01:29:55,246 --> 01:29:58,731
This main character... the "idiot woman"...

585
01:29:58,766 --> 01:30:00,891
Is it alright to tell you my opinion?

586
01:30:00,931 --> 01:30:03,911
For the main character...

587
01:30:03,946 --> 01:30:06,856
I'd like to go with her.

588
01:30:06,891 --> 01:30:09,891
Of course, you know her pretty well, too.

589
01:30:10,891 --> 01:30:13,211
She's really popular right now, right?

590
01:30:14,211 --> 01:30:18,891
Actually, I'm the one who first discovered and brought up Ginga.

591
01:30:20,211 --> 01:30:22,891
I'd like to work with her again.

592
01:30:24,211 --> 01:30:27,211
She's on your program pretty often, isn't she?

593
01:30:28,211 --> 01:30:30,211
I'm sorry, but...

594
01:30:32,211 --> 01:30:34,851
Could you ask her to make the movie with me?

595
01:30:34,886 --> 01:30:37,491
It'd be faster than talking with her manager.

596
01:30:37,526 --> 01:30:40,211
And it's your screenplay. Can you do it?

597
01:30:40,246 --> 01:30:42,211
This is a big chance for you.

598
01:30:43,731 --> 01:30:46,211
Hey... Izawa!

599
01:30:51,211 --> 01:30:56,011
Studio #1- "Imperial Special"- 's run-through will be conducted at 3 o'clock.

600
01:30:57,011 --> 01:30:59,731
Studio #1's run-through will begin at 3 o'clock.

601
01:31:08,211 --> 01:31:09,656
My candy!

602
01:31:09,691 --> 01:31:12,211
Someone, bring me my candy!

603
01:31:12,691 --> 01:31:15,211
Please.

604
01:31:56,931 --> 01:31:58,931
Unwrap it.

605
01:32:25,251 --> 01:32:26,891
I don't like those eyes.

606
01:32:26,926 --> 01:32:28,731
Don't look at me!

607
01:32:32,251 --> 01:32:34,696
Disgusting eyes...

608
01:32:34,731 --> 01:32:36,531
I'd like to hollow them out.

609
01:32:39,851 --> 01:32:42,651
Do you think that I'm Satan?

610
01:32:52,651 --> 01:32:53,851
Pick it up.

611
01:33:09,811 --> 01:33:11,131
Why don't you eat it?

612
01:33:13,811 --> 01:33:15,096
It's delicious.

613
01:33:15,131 --> 01:33:17,131
With my saliva all over it.

614
01:33:27,731 --> 01:33:29,131
Pig.

615
01:34:06,731 --> 01:34:08,651
Ginga, Happy Birthday.

616
01:34:08,686 --> 01:34:10,131
Thank you!

617
01:34:11,651 --> 01:34:14,131
Today Ginga is especially beautiful.

618
01:34:14,451 --> 01:34:18,211
Don't stare at her so much. The aftermath is pretty scary.

619
01:34:32,251 --> 01:34:36,251
Oh, isn't this a surprise? Meeting you here.

620
01:34:36,611 --> 01:34:40,851
Is it strange that I'm here? The first person to discover Ginga was me, anyway.

621
01:34:42,451 --> 01:34:44,851
And that's the one thing you always complain about.

622
01:34:45,851 --> 01:34:49,411
You're one to talk. Stealing her from me...

623
01:34:52,051 --> 01:34:54,376
But it's rather impressive.

624
01:34:54,411 --> 01:34:56,451
Getting along with the bureau director, huh?

625
01:34:56,771 --> 01:34:59,451
You sure have gotten ahead in life.

626
01:35:00,211 --> 01:35:02,851
How many men have you crushed by now?

627
01:35:05,451 --> 01:35:07,851
This isn't a place for losers.

628
01:35:20,971 --> 01:35:23,851
Ginga, you should dance too.

629
01:35:23,886 --> 01:35:25,416
Dance, Ginga.

630
01:35:25,451 --> 01:35:27,451
You want me to dance?

631
01:35:27,486 --> 01:35:28,908
I'm expensive.

632
01:35:28,943 --> 01:35:30,331
Come on. Dance!

633
01:35:30,691 --> 01:35:32,591
I don't want to dance today.

634
01:35:32,626 --> 01:35:34,456
You shouldn't dance, Ginga.

635
01:35:34,491 --> 01:35:38,331
It's my request, Ginga. Dance for me, the bureau director.

636
01:35:38,366 --> 01:35:41,096
No, Ginga. Don't dance.

637
01:35:41,131 --> 01:35:44,096
Do I have to dance for free?

638
01:35:44,131 --> 01:35:46,651
If you dance for me, I'll give you anything.

639
01:35:47,451 --> 01:35:49,136
Really? Anything?

640
01:35:49,171 --> 01:35:51,671
Anything. Today is your 20th birthday.

641
01:35:51,706 --> 01:35:54,171
If you want something, just tell me.

642
01:35:55,171 --> 01:35:57,136
Do you really promise?

643
01:35:57,171 --> 01:36:04,171
Hey. Who do you think I am? Whether it be a tank or a platoon, I can give you anything.

644
01:36:04,206 --> 01:36:05,971
Well, then I'll dance.

645
01:36:06,571 --> 01:36:07,691
Ginga...

646
01:38:37,171 --> 01:38:39,851
Wonderful, Ginga. You were wonderful.

647
01:38:39,886 --> 01:38:42,416
So, you'll give me what I want?

648
01:38:42,451 --> 01:38:47,091
Whatever you want. Clothes? Cars? Jewelry?

649
01:38:48,571 --> 01:38:50,616
On a silver plate...

650
01:38:50,651 --> 01:38:54,451
On a silver plate... what?

651
01:38:56,171 --> 01:38:58,171
A mountain of candy?

652
01:39:00,691 --> 01:39:02,171
Izawa's head.

653
01:39:05,771 --> 01:39:07,571
Izawa's head...

654
01:39:08,691 --> 01:39:10,571
Who's Izawa?

655
01:39:44,171 --> 01:39:45,611
This is great.

656
01:40:07,651 --> 01:40:13,571
Ginga, how do you wanna... cook this guy?

657
01:40:16,171 --> 01:40:17,571
Leave.

658
01:40:18,451 --> 01:40:19,571
Everyone, leave.

659
01:40:21,451 --> 01:40:22,576
Leave!

660
01:40:22,611 --> 01:40:23,811
Get out of here!

661
01:40:23,891 --> 01:40:26,171
Everyone, get out of here!

662
01:40:26,206 --> 01:40:27,656
What's wrong, Ginga?

663
01:40:27,691 --> 01:40:29,171
Everyone, get out of here!

664
01:40:31,971 --> 01:40:32,891
Stop it!

665
01:40:34,891 --> 01:40:37,891
Hurry up! What are you doing? Get out of here!

666
01:40:37,926 --> 01:40:38,891
Hurry!

667
01:40:39,211 --> 01:40:41,891
Go away! Everyone!

668
01:40:43,211 --> 01:40:44,711
Get out of here!

669
01:40:44,746 --> 01:40:46,211
Everyone, leave!

670
01:40:50,691 --> 01:40:52,211
Ginga.

671
01:40:53,211 --> 01:40:54,371
You too. Get out of here.

672
01:41:26,411 --> 01:41:29,211
A lot of people died today.

673
01:41:31,571 --> 01:41:37,491
Over here and over there, lots of idiots are dying.

674
01:41:51,611 --> 01:41:53,811
You look pathetic.

675
01:41:56,971 --> 01:41:59,811
I thought I told you to stop looking at me like that!

676
01:42:02,891 --> 01:42:05,131
You look horrible.

677
01:42:05,891 --> 01:42:08,131
Just horrible.

678
01:42:09,211 --> 01:42:11,611
Why don't you quit working here?

679
01:42:12,211 --> 01:42:15,211
You could quit any time you want.

680
01:42:15,246 --> 01:42:18,211
Why are you always getting in my way?

681
01:42:22,211 --> 01:42:23,851
An honest man.

682
01:42:23,886 --> 01:42:25,456
But just honest.

683
01:42:25,491 --> 01:42:28,011
That's why you can't become a bad person.

684
01:42:28,211 --> 01:42:31,211
Good things and bad things... You don't judge anything...

685
01:42:31,611 --> 01:42:33,336
Saying nothing and doing nothing...

686
01:42:33,371 --> 01:42:36,731
It's almost like you're being wise like an old man.

687
01:42:37,731 --> 01:42:39,211
You're so great.

688
01:42:40,731 --> 01:42:43,691
Really you think that I'm pitiable, don't you?

689
01:42:45,611 --> 01:42:49,691
You also think that yourself and the war are pitiable.

690
01:42:50,211 --> 01:42:53,691
Just like God, you're watching life from outside the world.

691
01:42:55,211 --> 01:42:57,491
How noble of you.

692
01:42:59,491 --> 01:43:03,731
Well, you know what? I don't like or dislike this world, either.

693
01:43:03,766 --> 01:43:07,211
I don't really care if the world is destroyed or anything.

694
01:43:07,246 --> 01:43:09,696
But, I am different from you

695
01:43:09,731 --> 01:43:12,976
in that I'm trying my hardest to live.

696
01:43:13,011 --> 01:43:17,211
I like desperately living like a bug, ugly and frantically flailing arms and legs.

697
01:43:18,211 --> 01:43:20,711
I could kill you right now.

698
01:43:20,746 --> 01:43:23,211
Because humans die so easily.

699
01:43:27,251 --> 01:43:31,251
Because... living is so much harder...

700
01:43:42,211 --> 01:43:46,931
I saw eyes like yours a long time ago.

701
01:43:51,651 --> 01:43:53,931
The eyes of someone determined...

702
01:44:01,931 --> 01:44:07,251
When I was a child, my house was burned down and I fled with my mother.

703
01:44:10,251 --> 01:44:16,531
Right before my eyes, a man was being beaten by a crowd of men.

704
01:44:19,411 --> 01:44:22,176
Because the man wasn't Japanese...

705
01:44:22,211 --> 01:44:26,211
There wasn't any real reason, but the man was lynched anyway.

706
01:44:27,731 --> 01:44:32,411
The man, noticing us, looked in our direction.

707
01:44:35,411 --> 01:44:38,931
Then the men who were beating him noticed us.

708
01:44:41,931 --> 01:44:45,211
They asked the man...

709
01:44:46,731 --> 01:44:49,251
"Is that your family?"

710
01:44:53,251 --> 01:44:57,731
The man, while staring at us, replied...

711
01:45:02,731 --> 01:45:04,731
"No. "

712
01:45:08,771 --> 01:45:11,211
They were chilling eyes.

713
01:45:14,051 --> 01:45:16,651
Determined eyes...

714
01:45:17,651 --> 01:45:20,211
They were the eyes of one awaiting death.

715
01:45:23,731 --> 01:45:26,731
This time the men asked us.

716
01:45:28,731 --> 01:45:31,731
"Is this your father?"

717
01:45:36,811 --> 01:45:39,731
I was scared and couldn't say anything.

718
01:45:42,971 --> 01:45:45,216
So I ran.

719
01:45:45,251 --> 01:45:48,451
I ran for a while and then turned around.

720
01:45:49,251 --> 01:45:52,411
I couldn't see the man anymore.

721
01:45:54,411 --> 01:45:57,771
Because the group of men had surrounded the man and wouldn't stop beating him.

722
01:45:58,771 --> 01:46:02,211
My mother pulled me by my hand and we ran and ran.

723
01:46:02,251 --> 01:46:05,211
But no matter where we went, it was Hell.

724
01:46:07,651 --> 01:46:12,651
But... what had burned into my eyes...

725
01:46:14,651 --> 01:46:15,851
those eyes...

726
01:46:17,251 --> 01:46:18,851
That look...

727
01:46:21,731 --> 01:46:25,451
The eyes of a determined man...

728
01:46:27,451 --> 01:46:30,451
The look of a man challenging death...

729
01:46:34,771 --> 01:46:37,451
The same as your eyes.

730
01:46:41,251 --> 01:46:43,451
This is ridiculous.

731
01:46:43,491 --> 01:46:48,451
Determined people, people who scoff at those things... All humans are worthless.

732
01:46:48,771 --> 01:46:50,096
It's so stupid.

733
01:46:50,131 --> 01:46:55,096
It's hilarious. I laugh at it.

734
01:46:55,131 --> 01:47:00,171
This world and all its people can die at my feet, looking up at me.

735
01:47:00,651 --> 01:47:02,136
I'll live on.

736
01:47:02,171 --> 01:47:05,971
I'll live on, crushing people as I dance.

737
01:47:06,006 --> 01:47:07,171
Is that strange?

738
01:47:07,206 --> 01:47:08,171
Am I crazy?

739
01:47:08,651 --> 01:47:10,551
I'm scared of dying.

740
01:47:10,586 --> 01:47:12,416
I don't want to die.

741
01:47:12,451 --> 01:47:14,691
That's why I'm scared of you.

742
01:47:15,171 --> 01:47:17,451
Your honesty scares me.

743
01:47:19,131 --> 01:47:22,691
When I look at you, I come to my senses.

744
01:47:25,171 --> 01:47:30,171
If I come to my senses, I won't be able to live any more.

745
01:47:52,651 --> 01:47:54,651
Don't come here ever again.

746
01:48:29,651 --> 01:48:32,616
I'm 20 now.

747
01:48:32,651 --> 01:48:35,616
We should have a huge party.

748
01:48:35,651 --> 01:48:38,891
I'll wear clothes that will make everyone jealous...

749
01:48:39,891 --> 01:48:44,691
Everyone will celebrate my birthday on a simultaneous national broadcast

750
01:48:59,691 --> 01:49:01,651
Help me...

751
01:49:46,651 --> 01:49:47,651
What's wrong?

752
01:50:36,651 --> 01:50:38,651
Was I dreaming?

753
01:50:39,171 --> 01:50:45,171
No... Is there proof that even this reality isn't a dream?

754
01:51:16,171 --> 01:51:22,136
I wanted to make sure... of my lost time...

755
01:51:22,171 --> 01:51:28,451
...of her shadow... her skin... her existence...

756
01:51:30,451 --> 01:51:35,171
More than that, I had to verify my own existence.

757
01:51:39,171 --> 01:51:40,971
Where am I?

758
01:54:28,411 --> 01:54:30,171
Do you like them?

759
01:54:52,571 --> 01:54:55,171
This one is better made.

760
01:54:59,171 --> 01:55:05,171
These stones. They are saying that they want a face.

761
01:55:06,771 --> 01:55:09,171
that they want me to draw them a face.

762
01:55:12,691 --> 01:55:16,211
You know what you are, right?

763
01:55:20,211 --> 01:55:25,211
These stones also know that they are stones.

764
01:55:30,171 --> 01:55:34,171
What separates men from stones?

765
01:55:36,571 --> 01:55:37,891
Is it wisdom?

766
01:55:40,891 --> 01:55:42,891
Is it life?

767
01:55:42,926 --> 01:55:43,691
No.

768
01:55:46,891 --> 01:55:48,891
It's a face.

769
01:55:52,611 --> 01:55:55,891
Because it lacks a face, it is just a stone.

770
01:56:01,691 --> 01:56:08,211
Because it has a face, you are you and I am me.

771
01:56:10,211 --> 01:56:14,571
But if you didn't have a face...

772
01:56:15,211 --> 01:56:18,536
and if I didn't have a face...

773
01:56:18,571 --> 01:56:21,171
there is nothing to separate you from me.

774
01:56:25,171 --> 01:56:27,171
It is the same with a stone.

775
01:56:29,691 --> 01:56:35,171
You are I are only stones with faces.

776
01:56:35,891 --> 01:56:45,211
There are tens of thousands of stones with faces jumbled together in this world.

777
01:57:31,211 --> 01:57:32,571
She is...

778
01:57:35,211 --> 01:57:36,571
Sayo is...

779
01:57:37,491 --> 01:57:39,571
a stone without a face.

780
01:57:41,571 --> 01:57:44,611
That's because she is a part of her hometown.

781
01:57:44,646 --> 01:57:47,891
Humans need a hometown.

782
01:57:51,731 --> 01:57:54,691
Things other than humans also have hometowns.

783
01:57:55,691 --> 01:58:05,211
Dogs... cats... even stones have hometowns...

784
01:58:07,211 --> 01:58:12,611
In the end, everyone returns to their hometown.

785
01:58:19,211 --> 01:58:30,611
One rakes up the helplessness of the world.

786
01:58:30,646 --> 01:58:41,576
Secretly the dream has become clear.

787
01:58:41,611 --> 01:58:53,611
One rakes up the helplessness of the world.

788
01:58:54,611 --> 01:59:07,731
Secretly the dream has become clear.

789
01:59:48,211 --> 01:59:51,211
Mother... Mother...

790
01:59:53,611 --> 01:59:54,411
Mother...

791
01:59:56,611 --> 01:59:57,731
Mother...

792
02:01:24,731 --> 02:01:26,731
Go home.

793
02:01:28,251 --> 02:01:30,251
You shouldn't be here.

794
02:01:59,211 --> 02:02:00,211
Aki!

795
02:02:01,931 --> 02:02:04,176
Where did she go with that baby?

796
02:02:04,211 --> 02:02:11,251
Mr. Izawa, I thought that we'd be okay for another 4 or 5 days, but this town is finally over too.

797
02:02:11,286 --> 02:02:13,251
Let's run away together.

798
02:02:22,211 --> 02:02:24,691
Run away? To where?

799
02:02:25,211 --> 02:02:28,176
This time I had made up my mind.

800
02:02:28,211 --> 02:02:32,211
The great love of war would solve everything.

801
02:03:27,211 --> 02:03:30,176
Mr. Izawa, I'm going to get out of here.

802
02:03:30,211 --> 02:03:34,251
I don't want to stay around and die in smoke.

803
02:03:38,731 --> 02:03:41,251
Good luck.

804
02:06:47,211 --> 02:06:51,211
This is my final film.

805
02:08:51,211 --> 02:08:55,731
Miss Sayo, let's run away together.

806
02:11:08,731 --> 02:11:10,731
So pretty...

807
02:14:00,731 --> 02:14:03,216
Don't go over there!

808
02:14:03,251 --> 02:14:05,031
If you go there, you'll only die.

809
02:14:05,066 --> 02:14:06,811
When you die, we'll do it together.

810
02:14:07,611 --> 02:14:08,811
Don't be scared!

811
02:14:09,611 --> 02:14:10,811
And don't leave me.

812
02:14:11,251 --> 02:14:15,851
Forget about the fire and the bombs and we'll go down this street together.

813
02:14:15,886 --> 02:14:18,851
Look straight ahead down this street and hold onto my shoulder.

814
02:14:19,771 --> 02:14:20,851
Alright?

815
02:14:21,611 --> 02:14:22,851
You got it?

816
02:16:57,731 --> 02:17:01,531
Is she alright? Is she injured?

817
02:17:03,251 --> 02:17:06,531
Be brave and hold on.

818
02:17:24,211 --> 02:17:30,731
I took the idiot woman's hand and walked on and on.

819
02:17:31,251 --> 02:17:37,651
We walk endlessly down the eternal path.

